FBIS4-21882 "jptot015__l94047" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 3 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA PALESTINIAN AFFAIRS Collaborator Killed; Hamas Man Dies in Clash With Fatah Collaborator Killed; Hamas Man Dies in Clash With Fatah TA0304103894 Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST in English 3 Apr 94 p 2 TA0304103894 Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST English BFN [Report by ITIM] [Excerpts] [passage omitted] Fayiz Hindi, 45, of the Jabalyah refugee camp, was murdered yesterday, apparently by Fatah Hawks who suspected him of collaborating with the authorities. The assailants also pumped five bullets into the legs of Hindi's brother, Salah, 42, who survived. The brothers had been kidnapped from their home by the Hawks on Friday. [passage omitted] Muhammad Mahir, a 31-year-old Rafah resident and Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] supporter, died yesterday of wounds suffered when he was shot two weeks ago in a clash between local Hamas and Fatah activists. [passage omitted]
